'''Ahmed Mohamed Aboelfetouh Mohamed''' ({{langx|ar|أحمد محمد أبو الفتوح محمد}}; born 22 March 1998), simply known as '''Ahmed Fatouh''' ({{langx|ar|أحمد فتوح}}), is an Egyptian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Egyptian Premier League]] side [[Zamalek SC|Zamalek]] and the [[Egypt national football team|Egypt national team]] as a [[left-back]] or [[left wing-back]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/ahmed-aboel-fettoh/480336/ |title=Ahmed Abou El Fotouh - Player profile |work=Soccerway |accessdate=27 March 2019}}</ref>

Fatouh featured in the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations Final]] against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Mayo|first=Marc|date=6 February 2022|title=How Egypt will line up against Senegal tonight|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/egypt-xi-vs-senegal-starting-lineup-confirmed-team-news-injury-covid-latest-afcon-final-2022-today-b980902.html|access-date=6 February 2022|website=www.standard.co.uk|language=en}}</ref>

